From 4223e89c397603327d197aa8f3e01f97933a4199 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vivek Chettri <vchettri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 5 Aug 2025 20:53:13 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK: DP: wifi: ath12k: Update TCL fields for SDWF DS in
 slow/reinject path

The initial few packets for SDWF in PPE DS mode would
be handled by the driver either in the slow path or reinject path.

In either case, the fast_xmit field would not be set unlike SFE.
In such cases, if the SDWF valid bit is set, update the required
fields of the TCL descriptor required for SDWF.

Signed-off-by: Vivek Chettri <vchettri@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
index 910efad..2bfff09 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
@@ -1295,6 +1295,15 @@ skip_htt_metadata:
 
 	ath12k_wifi7_hal_tx_cmd_desc_setup(ab, hal_tcl_desc, &ti);
 
+	/* For SDWF DS support, either the slow packet or the
+	 * reinject packets would not have skb->fast_xmit set
+	 * and the msduq information should be updated if the
+	 * SDWF is valid in skb->mark
+	 */
+	if (unlikely(skb->mark & SDWF_VALID_MASK))
+		ath12k_dp_qos_update(dp, dp_pdev, skb->mark, hal_tcl_desc,
+				     0, NULL);
+
 	if (unlikely(arsta)) {
 		qos_tag = ath12k_get_qos_tag(skb->mark);
 		if (qos_tag)
-- 
